Pointer A travels:
A + B = 11 nodes

Pointer B travels:
B + A = 11 nodes

Both cover exactly the same distance.
The extra nodes at the beginning of one list get cancelled when they switch lists. that's why we don't need:
length calculation
hashing
nested loop

***Why does the loop condition use: pointerA != pointerB  and not  pointerA->val != pointerB->val?***
In this problem, intersection means both lists share the exact same node in memory, not just the same value.IT wants the shared node, 
not a node with the same value. 

